      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Interesting! I found some key things:\n\n1. `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\cognitive-taxonomy-vscode-ext` - This looks like a VS Code extension they recently built!\n2. `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.antigravity-ide` - This exists and was modified on 02/06/2026, so they already have an antigravity-ide project\n3. `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.securecoder` - Another project they recently worked on\n4. `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.copilot` - Another project\n\nLet me look at the cognitive-taxonomy-vscode-ext README and the antigravity-ide folder more closely to understand what they built.\n\n\nI'll start by reading through the documentation for both projects to get a clearer picture of what each one does.",
