    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "write",
      "code": "{\"content\": \"# Antigravity Taxonomy Protocol\\n\\n**Antigravity IDE Edition** \\u2014 A five-colour architectural taxonomy built into Antigravity IDE. Shifts code comprehension from **System 2** (linear reading) to **System 1** (pattern recognition).\\n\\n> Built from the [Cognitive Taxonomy Protocol](https://github.com/) for VS Code. This version is bundled with Antigravity IDE.\\n\\n## How It Works\\n\\nToggle with `Ctrl+Shift+G` (or `Cmd+Shift+G` on Mac). Watch the bottom-right status bar: `Antigravity: ON` / `Antigravity: OFF`.\\n\\n### Taxonomy Mode\\n\\n- Each line gets a **coloured left border** by architectural category\\n- Hover over any line to see a **tooltip** explaining what it does\\n- VS Code Dark+ token colours are neutralised to grey\\n- Comments stay green (preserved)\\n- Sidebar panel shows cognitive load metrics and data flow diagrams\\n\\n### Categories\\n\\n| Colour | Category | What It Means |\\n|--------|----------|---------------|\\n| Blue | Blueprint | Data structures \\u2014 what we're building |\\n| Green | Plumbing | Infrastructure \\u2014 how it connects |\\n| Orange | Transaction | Logic flow \\u2014 how data moves |\\n| Red | Constraint | Hard limits \\u2014 what cannot be exceeded |\\n| Purple | Pedagogy | Assessment \\u2014 how this is graded |\\n\\n## Key Features\\n\\n- **Plain-English tooltips** \\u2014 every line explained in accessible language, like a good mentor\\n- **Cognitive load metrics** \\u2014 maintainability score, balance score, overall load indicator\\n- **Data flow diagrams** \\u2014 4 view modes: ASCII, Mini, Mermaid, SVG\\n- **Architecture map** \\u2014 visual spatial layout of the five categories\\n- **Code smell detection** \\u2014 flags potential issues in your code\\n- **Sidebar panel** \\u2014 navigable line-by-line breakdown with category filters\\n\\n## Keyboard Shortcuts\\n\\n| Shortcut | Action |\\n|----------|--------|\\n| `Ctrl+Shift+G` | Toggle Antigravity taxonomy view |\\n| `Ctrl+Shift+H` | Cycle data flow view mode |\\n\\n## Install (Development)\\n\\n```bash\\ncd extensions/cognitive-taxonomy-antigravity-0.0.1-universal\\nnpm install\\nnpm run compile\\n```\\n\\nThen in Antigravity IDE:\\n1. Press `F5` to launch Extension Development Host\\n2. Open a Python file\\n3. Press `Ctrl+Shift+G` to toggle taxonomy mode\\n\\n## Grounded In\\n\\n- **Kahneman (2011)** \\u2014 System 1/System 2 dual-process theory\\n- **Miller (1956)** \\u2014 Working memory limit: 7\\u00b12 chunks (five colours stays within)\\n- **Sarkar (2015)** \\u2014 Syntax highlighting improves comprehension for novices\\n- **Asenov et al. (2016)** \\u2014 Richer visualisations reduce comprehension time by 75%\\n- **MITRE ATT&CK** \\u2014 Taxonomy-based visual compression transformed cybersecurity\\n\", \"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\.antigravity-ide\\\\extensions\\\\cognitive-taxonomy-antigravity-0.0.1-universal\\\\README.md\"}",
      "output": "Wrote file successfully.",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1781534996890
    },
