      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I have all 4 design iterations. Let me analyze the design tokens:\n\n**Color palette:**\n- `--blue: #3b82f6` (Blueprint)\n- `--green: #10b981` (Plumbing)\n- `--orange: #f97316` (Transaction)\n- `--red: #ef4444` (Constraint)\n- `--purple: #a855f7` (Pedagogy)\n- `--bg: #0f0f0f` / `#1e1e1e` (background)\n- `--text: #e0e0e0` / `#d4d4d4` (text)\n\n\n- `--muted: #888` / `#858585` (muted)\n- `--border: #2a2a2a` / `#333` (borders)\n- `--code-bg: #111` / `#1e1e1e` (code background)\n\n**Typography:**\n- Font stack: `'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif`\n- Code font: `'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', 'Cascadia Code', 'Consolas', monospace`\n- H1 gradient: rainbow gradient spanning the five category colors\n- Body text color: `#e0e0e0` or `#d4d4d4`, muted at `#888` or `#858585`\n\n**Layout & UI components:**\n- Container maxes out at 1200px with centered layout and 2rem padding\n- Card styling uses dark backgrounds like `#1a1a1a`, `#252526`, with `8px` or `6px` border radius and 1px borders\n- Toggle buttons: 56×28px pill shape with white knob that slides 28px when active\n- Code panels have darker backgrounds with 1px borders and headers in a slightly lighter shade\n- Legend uses flexbox wrapping with gap spacing and 12-14px rounded dot indicators\n\n**Motion & effects:**\n- Toggle transitions at 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1) for smooth knob movement\n- Taxonomy mode applies subtle background tints at 10-15% opacity with colored left borders\n- Line highlighting on hover uses brightness filtering for interactive feedback\n- All color changes transition at 0.35-0.4s for seamless mode switching\n\nNow I'm mapping out the full site structure: a multi-page documentation with an interactive homepage, VS Code extension and Antigravity IDE sections that explain how to install and configure the system, and supporting pages for the research background, installation guides, and navigation. I'm planning the file structure with separate HTML, CSS, and JS directories for a vanilla setup, plus a root index.html that ties everything together.\n\nThis is a substantial undertaking, so I need to be strategic about the build. I'll create a `site/` directory to house the complete project, then generate each page methodically—starting with the global CSS that pulls from the design tokens, then the main pages with their specific styles, and finally the JavaScript for interactivity. For Netlify deployment, I'll include the necessary config file to ensure smooth hosting.",
      "timestamp": 1781535305928
    },
    {
